BREAKING: Emir Of Kano, Sanusi, Dethroned
68 Comments
9 Hours Ago Kano State Executive Council approved the dethronement at a special sitting held on Monday. Since coming on the throne, Sanusi, who rose to become Governor of Nigeria’s Central Bank as a professional, has always spoken out against harmful traditions and practices in the North, often times drawing the ire of elites in the region. The executive council headed by Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano claimed that Sanusi was removed for displaying disregard for laid down rules.